    <h2 >5 YEARS HISTORY OF THE CHURCH</h2>


    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-5 col-md-6 col-sm-offset-2 col-md-offset-0">
                <h3 style="text-align:left"><u>THE VISION</u></h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col" style="text-align:justify">
                The Head Pastor of Ascension Baptist Church, Bomso (Reverend Anthony Badu) had the
                vision to plant a church in Appiadu after the church had celebrated her 25th Anniversary. He
                therefore engaged Evangelism and Mission Board to see to the planting of the church. The
                Head Pastor, Evangelism and Missions Board (chaired by Retired Rev. Martin Yaw
                Afoakwah) and the then Youth Ministry President (led by Pastor Richmond Osei Bonsu of
                Central Charismatic Baptist Church - Gyinyase) in the Kumasi South West Baptist
                Association paid an honourable visit to the chief of Appiadu (the late Odeefour Owusu
                Amoaye II) of their intention to plant a church on his stool land. The chief and two of his
                elders welcomed them and assured them of their intention to release any size of land for the
                building of the church.
            </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col">
                <h3 style="text-align:left"><u>THE ORGANIZATION</u></h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col" style="text-align:justify">
                The Youth Ministry came and settled on the 1st of March, 2017 to pray and go on dawn
                broadcasting, creating the awareness of an impending crusade to be organised in the town. On
                Thursday 2
                nd and Friday 3rd
                of March, 2017, Crusade was organised in the evening at
                6:30pm. On Thursday evening, there was a heavy rain fall but the Lord made a way for the
                programme to continue. Reverend Augustine Osei Bonsu of Family Baptist-Anwomaso
                preached on that evening.
                The programme continued on Friday with word ministration given by Reverend Anthony
                Badu. The two days programme was successful as people came out giving their lives to
                Christ.
                The programme continued on Saturday 4th March, 2017 with Medical Screening and
                presentation of items to the people of the community. There was also house-to-house
                evangelism in the afternoon.
                Church Service was held on Sunday morning of 5th March, 2017. The service was honoured
                by some dignitaries from the late Odeefour Owusu Amoaye II (Appiaduhene). The service
                sermon was presented by Reverend Anthony Badu. The recorded new converts of about 18.

            </div>
        </div>
