Appiadu. The land developed litigation issues which caused the church to lose the land. The 
church did not relent in her pursuit for a different land. With the help of God, Deacon and 
Deaconess Osei, the leadership of Appiadu and the mother church (Bomso) headed by Rev.
Anthony Yaw Badu helped the church to acquire our current land.
On Thursday 30th July, 2020 the church started clearing the land for construction and since 
then, this is how far the LORD has brought us (Ebenezer).


            </div>
